<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54135b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54135b">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54135b"> 135(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> wait till wind fills / sails</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There we may note the parti-coloured sail with its variegated stripes, and the rich carving of stem and stern. These magnificent sails were a source of much pride to their possessors, and the story is told of Sigurd Jerusalem-farer that on his way home from Jerusalem to Constantinople he lay for half-a-month off Cape Malea, <mark>waiting for a side wind, so that his sails might be set lengthwise along the ship</mark> and so be better seen by those standing on shore as he sailed up to Constantinople. <small> Allen Mawers, <a name="VIK2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#VIK2"><cite title="source">The Vikings</cite></a> (1913) 100</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
